                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Indore, Sept. 14 (PTI): A drunk man today entered the engine room of the Mhow-Ratlam Fast Passenger with hundreds of passengers on board and drove it for some distance before it was stopped.          
	Golu Jagtap entered when the train was on a platform and the driver and his assistant were not there. As the engine was on, he pulled the train to some distance. When the driver and his assistant saw the train chugging off, they rushed in and stopped it. Golu has been arrested.                  
	 Bhubaneswar (PTI): The Election Commission will distribute photo-identity cards among new voters at 10 lakh centres across the country on January 25, 2011, election commissioner V.S. Sampath has said.                  
	 Hyderabad (PTI): An oil spill over 3 to 5sqkm has been spotted along the coast in Andhra Pradeshs East Godavari district. Officials said they found black oil spill near Surasani Yanam village where Ravva oil fields are located. It is not clear how the spill occurred.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Supreme Court has ruled that though the father is the natural guardian, maternal grandparents or other relatives can be given custody of a child as welfare of the minor is of paramount consideration. The court set aside a Bombay High Court order to give custody of a minor to the maternal grandparents as the father had remarried shortly after the death of his first wife and was also not in a position to look after the child.
                                                                                                                                              
